						<summary>

						<p>Slab in the Chennakēśva temple.</p>						

						<p>This is dated in the cyclic year <hi rend="bold">Siddhārthi ba. 7, Monday.</hi> On the basis of palaeography, it may be assigned to the 15th century A.D.</p>						

						<p>It records a gift of land out of the god's holding (Perumāḍla-<hi rend="italic">vritti</hi>) by Bhaṇḍāri-Nāyuḍu and three other persons (names are given) to Nandi Anantu for the merit of Valabayya and his wife Avubhaḷakka and others.</p>						

						</summary>
